				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\nabla {{\rm{\Phi }}}_{x}=\frac{{\lambda }_{0}}{{P}_{x}}$$\end{document}, where the Px is the periodicity of the unit-cell in the x-direction. For instance, we assumed Px = 1200 nm, so the cut-off wavelength of our metasurface is λ0 = 1200 nm.

